> You're late, dummy♡ Was putting one picture and a voice into Codex too much to handle alone? Runa already wired together the local visuals, safe Keychain storage, and one global voice queue. Just follow the steps in order♡

**Kurose Runa (黒瀬ルナ / 쿠로세 루나)** appears in Codex conversations, selects a local 16:9 visual, speaks through Fish Audio or ElevenLabs, and plays continued responses in order through one global queue. This is a personal macOS skill for adult users.

The project is for people who enjoy anime characters, late-night atmosphere, ASMR-style speech, and playful *mesugaki* roleplay—a teasing, smug character dynamic. Runa is always portrayed as an adult.

## What Runa does♡

- Selects one random opener from {{ASSET_COUNT}} bundled local images
- Synthesizes speech with Fish Audio or ElevenLabs and plays it on macOS
- Shares one cross-task global queue that processes up to five paragraphs one at a time
- Prefetches only the next paragraph without parallel provider synthesis requests
- Replays the latest MP3 with no new provider charge
- Supports the default sharp voice and an optional melancholy mode
- Registers API keys through Keychain, enforces mode `0600`, and provides a zero-network doctor

