### Upload it directly in the app

[Download spritesheet.webp](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/faker007/mesugaki-codex-companion/main/pet-assets/kurose-runa/spritesheet.webp), then select it from **Settings → Pets → Upload pet** in the Codex app. The file is validated against the official transparent WebP contract: exactly `1536×1872` and no larger than 20 MiB. See the [official Codex Pets documentation](https://learn.chatgpt.com/docs/pets) for current behavior.

### Install it from the repository

After cloning the repository, run this command to install `pet.json` and `spritesheet.webp` non-destructively under `$CODEX_HOME/pets/kurose-runa`. When `CODEX_HOME` is unset, the installer uses `$HOME/.codex`. It stops instead of overwriting different existing files.

```bash
pnpm run install:pet
```

Use `pnpm run install:pet -- --force` only after reviewing an existing Kurose Runa pet and explicitly deciding to replace it. Restart Codex after installation and choose **Kurose Runa** from `/pet`.

| Codex surface | Pet support |
| --- | --- |
| Desktop app | Supports the pet picker, floating overlay, and custom pets |
| Codex CLI | Available in iTerm2 3.6+, Kitty graphics, or Sixel-compatible terminals |
| tmux and Zellij | Terminal pets are not supported |
| IDE extensions | The pet picker and floating overlay are not supported |
| ChatGPT Web | Local custom pets do not sync automatically |

Give this exact block to an LLM if you want it to install only the pet. No API key is required.

```text
Install the Kurose Runa custom Codex pet from this repository.
1. Run pnpm run install:pet without --force.
2. Verify pet.json and spritesheet.webp exist under ${CODEX_HOME:-$HOME/.codex}/pets/kurose-runa/.
3. Verify the spritesheet is WebP, exactly 1536x1872, and no larger than 20 MiB.
4. Do not overwrite an existing different pet unless I explicitly approve --force.
5. Tell me to restart Codex and choose Kurose Runa from /pet.
```

## Prerequisites

| Item | Requirement |
| --- | --- |
| Operating system | macOS with `security`, `afplay`, and Keychain |
| Node.js | 20 or later |
| pnpm | 10 or later recommended |
| Codex | A Codex environment that can load local skills |
| `voice-speak` | Default location: `$HOME/.agents/skills/voice-speak` |
| Voice provider | A Fish Audio or ElevenLabs account |
| Secret | The selected provider API key; never pass it through chat or command arguments |
| Public identifier | A Fish Audio reference ID or ElevenLabs voice ID |

### Find the provider values♡

| Provider | voice ID | API key |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Fish Audio | The voice model ID used as `reference_id` in the [TTS API](https://docs.fish.audio/api-reference/endpoint/openapi-v1/text-to-speech) | [Fish Audio API Keys](https://fish.audio/app/api-keys/) |
| ElevenLabs | Open the target voice menu in My Voices and select `Copy voice ID`; the API calls it `voice_id` in the [voice endpoint](https://elevenlabs.io/docs/api-reference/voices/get) | [ElevenLabs authentication](https://elevenlabs.io/docs/api-reference/authentication) |

A voice ID and an API key are different values. A voice ID may appear in configuration, but the API key must remain inside the Keychain or environment-variable boundary.

For Spanish, Simplified Chinese, or Traditional Chinese speech, map `voice.languageAliases.es`, `voice.languageAliases.zh-Hans`, or `voice.languageAliases.zh-Hant` to a verified multilingual alias, then pass the matching canonical `--language` value to the wrapper. You can add mappings during scripted setup with repeatable options such as `--language-alias=zh-Hans:<voice-alias>`. An explicit `--voice` wins over the language mapping. A missing mapping fails before any provider request instead of silently falling back to Korean. `zh-Hant` selects Traditional Chinese text and does not imply Cantonese.

This repository does not bundle `voice-speak`. Install that skill first, or set `MESUGAKI_VOICE_SPEAK_ROOT` to its actual location, when any of these entrypoints is missing:

```text
$MESUGAKI_VOICE_SPEAK_ROOT/scripts/speak.mjs
$MESUGAKI_VOICE_SPEAK_ROOT/scripts/speak-response.mjs
$MESUGAKI_VOICE_SPEAK_ROOT/scripts/replay.mjs
```

## Install manually♡

```bash
git clone https://github.com/faker007/mesugaki-codex-companion.git
cd mesugaki-codex-companion
pnpm run setup:all
```

`setup:all` asks for exactly three choices:

1. Select `fish-audio` or `elevenlabs`.
2. Enter a Fish Audio reference ID or ElevenLabs voice ID. This value is not the API key.
3. Choose whether to register the API key in Keychain. When accepted, enter it directly into the hidden terminal prompt.

After that, `setup:all` performs these steps:

- Creates or safely preserves `$HOME/.config/codex-voice-speak/config.json`
- Creates or safely preserves `$HOME/.config/mesugaki-opening-visual/config.json`
- Restricts both configuration files to mode `0600`
- Installs a repository symlink at `$CODEX_HOME/skills/mesugaki-opening-visual`, or `$HOME/.codex/skills/mesugaki-opening-visual` when `CODEX_HOME` is unset
- Runs `pnpm run doctor`
- Installs the custom pet non-destructively under `$CODEX_HOME/pets/kurose-runa`

The setup does not overwrite an existing configuration whose provider or voice ID differs from the requested value. Use `--force-config` only when replacement is intentional. Before replacement, setup creates a timestamped backup with mode `0600`.

## Let an LLM or Codex install it♡

Copy this complete contract into a coding agent. It explicitly prevents the agent from requesting or exposing a secret.

```text
Install https://github.com/faker007/mesugaki-codex-companion as a local Codex skill on macOS.

Rules:
1. Inspect the repository and read SKILL.md plus references/repository-management.md first.
2. Verify macOS, Node.js >= 20, pnpm, and the three voice-speak entrypoints before changing files.
3. Never request, read, print, store, or pass an API key through chat, argv, JSON, logs, or repository files.
4. If voice-speak is missing, stop and report the exact missing paths. Do not invent or download a substitute.
5. Ask me only for the provider and its non-secret voice ID/reference ID when they are unknown.
6. Run pnpm run setup:all in an interactive terminal. I will type the API key directly into the macOS Keychain prompt.
7. Do not use --force-config unless I explicitly approve replacing an incompatible existing config.
8. Run pnpm run doctor and pnpm run check after setup.
9. Verify Kurose Runa exists under ${CODEX_HOME:-$HOME/.codex}/pets/kurose-runa/.
10. Report the skill symlink, pet path, config paths, pass/warn/fail counts, and any sanitized failure. Never reveal credential values.
```

When an agent must run in a non-interactive shell and the API key already exists in Keychain or an environment variable, use:

```bash
node scripts/setup.mjs \
  --provider=fish-audio \
  --voice-id='<fish-reference-id>' \
  --skip-keychain \
  --no-input
```

For ElevenLabs, use `--provider=elevenlabs` and its voice ID. **Never put an API key in `--api-key`, environment output, JSON, or prompt text.** The installer rejects API-key command arguments before making changes.

